{"id": "EUVD-2021-34502", "enisaUuid": "b10527b1-f45c-3762-ac9a-c2e8ab51d2de", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndm rq: don't queue request to blk-mq during DM suspend\n\nDM uses blk-mq's quiesce/unquiesce to stop/start device mapper queue.\n\nBut blk-mq's unquiesce may come from outside events, such as elevator\nswitch, updating nr_requests or others, and request may come during\nsuspend, so simply ask for blk-mq to requeue it.\n\nFixes one kernel panic issue when running updating nr_requests and\ndm-mpath suspend/resume stress test.", "datePublished": "2024-05-22T08:19:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-18T11:37:44", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ca9745efe3528feb06ca4e117188038eea2d351", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b4459b11e84092658fa195a2587aff3b9637f0e7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8050652810bf38241edec8717393d2446e8036f1", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-47498", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00007.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-47498"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "051aa2d0-9f71-3853-8c3e-d3373063077a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bfebd1cdb497a57757c83f5fbf1a29931591e2a4 <8050652810bf38241edec8717393d2446e8036f1"}, {"id": "184fb92c-77d3-3ce4-b0b7-b96a7eaf6de8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8050652810bf38241edec8717393d2446e8036f1"}, {"id": "1ed24f2e-95ad-363a-86f6-e8721c08ecc0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bfebd1cdb497a57757c83f5fbf1a29931591e2a4 <8ca9745efe3528feb06ca4e117188038eea2d351"}, {"id": "266748a2-0003-3e1b-8d22-98f1d63e3ea8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7b17c2f7292ba1f3f98dae3f7077f9e569653276 <b4459b11e84092658fa195a2587aff3b9637f0e7"}, {"id": "28e80457-017f-32df-b5d1-